<font color="#FF0000">THE TRUTH????</font><br>
<tt>Thu Jul 31 21:53:39 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Religion is that vehicle by which we purvey the &quot;word&quot; of God.  It is that instrument that allows us to believe that something is true because of the &quot;Truth of Tenacity,&quot; Something IS TRUE because I believe it to be true.<br>
 <br>
Another type of truth is the &quot;Truth of Authority,&quot; where something is true because Grandma told me so.<br>
  <br>
A third type of truth is the &quot;Truth of A Priori,&quot; which tells me something is true because of a GUT feeling, a combination of sensual intakes that seems to give that Gestaltic (bigger than the sum of its parts) feeling of a sixth sense.  <br>
The last type truth is that which we call the &quot;Empirical Truth,&quot; which is supported (supposedly) by math, science, and tedious examination.<br>
The truth of tenacity allows Eskimos on the top of the world to firmly believe that if women hunt, the animals will be offended and everyone will starve because of poor hunting.  This truth justifies infanticide for female children born without having an older brother who can supplement the family's food supply with his hunting activities.  Even a five-year-old boy can sit by an air hole and harpoon a seal.  If an older brother exists then the mother and father are delighted at the birth of a female child... if not then her tiny body is fed to the dog team.  No protein is wasted.<br>
The truth of authority will let you down.  For a long time the leading scientists told us that the world was flat.  The population embraced that truth and non-believer were killed as heritics.<br>
If you believe in the truth of a priori, then go to Las Vegas and see if your gut feelings will always pan out.  I am not saying that they don't sometimes.<br>
Empirical truth!  Have two people count a barrel full of B-B's and see if they come up with the same number.<br>
I have blindly believed that something was true and learned that I was right or that I was wrong.<br>
I have had authority figures give me the truth and also give me myth.<br>
I have followed gut feelings (hunting, fishing, gambling, predicting the weather, combat... etc.) only to lose sometimes and win enough times to cling to the practice.<br>
I have learned that empirical truth is only as valid and true as the methodology that constructs the experiment.  Mark Twain use to say something like...&quot;There are lies, damn lies and then there are statistics.&quot;<br>
Psychologically, our embracement of truth is sometimes affected by denial, emotions, and even temporary or permanent biological states.<br>
The tenacity of truth seems to work better if I am surrounded by a body of common believers who believe as I do.<br>
The truth of authority seems to work better if I happen to have unshaken respect for the &quot;elder or expert.&quot;  <br>
The truth of A priori seem to work better if I carefully evaluate my collective preceptions and make more good guesses than bad ones.<br>
Scientific discovery, of the empirical truth is always contaminated if I enter the process to prove that which I want to be proven.  Are we not biased as humans?<br>
Therefore, it seems prudent to advocate that no man has the answers, except for himself.  Under a free society he is allowed to persuade others, to search diligently, to assume, and gain reward or suffer consequence.  Certainly, realistically, in the ancient tradition...&quot;no man can tell another man what to do.&quot;<br>
I choose to believe that prophecies are fulfilled.  If I believe that I am a loser, I will become one.  If I choose to believe that I will succeed, then I usually do.<br>
If I believe that an Eagle or a Holy Ring has power, then it does.  If for no other reason than it serves to shape my prophecy.<br><br>
Here we will try to understand our beliefs about God, brotherhood, emotional injuries, warfare, government, parenting, healing and anything else which we choose to bring to the circle.  We will all grapple with truth as we perceive it.<br><br>
Together, we will walk off the battlefield... and we will leave no one behind.
